Follow her around as she discovers her past containing many dark secrets, sad moments, and more. The ultimate goal of the mod is to show a story never seen before in Doki mods.Current version: 1.0 [18th August 2020]

_data.title: The Last Sky
_data.description: Описание от автора: Данная модификация повествует о последних минутах жизни тяжело больного парня. О чём он думал перед смертью? Было ли что-то большое и светлое в его жизни?

_data.title: The New Literature Club
_data.description: A grand idea inspired this mod: what about a full-blown sequel to DDLC?The story takes place after the good ending of DDLC, with a self-aware Sayori thanking you for all you did (while Monika floats out in limbo after her deletion). Set two months after this event, our protagonist returns to the literature club after having drifted away from it to find a larger group of 7, now. He finds all three of the girls (Natsuki, Yuri, and of course, Sayori) in the club cute, and this sways him to join. Now, he must help the club get ready for the upcoming Winter Festival, all while trying to impress the girl of his fancy.This game will expand a lot of the features of DDLC. There is still poem writing, still drama between the club members, and still all the loveable quirks in the dialogue. However, this game will be much larger. Act 1 has 5 ways to end (though this trickles into only 3 distinct ways to play through Act 2). There are four new male characters, each with distinct personalities and ties to the Doki girls we know and love. It tackles how Sayori might deal with her self-awareness, in light of her depression, and also asks what the club would be like if it were larger. I won't delve too much further into detail, I'll let that be left for later.

_data.title: The Renewal
_data.description: In the beginning of the umpteenth loop of the game where all the dramatical events have always taken place, something changes. Out of nowhere, MC becomes self aware like Monika has always been. He remembers everything that happened in the past and will try his best to save everyone from their cruel fates (yes, even Monika). The thing is, something will be in the way, and he will quickly notice it... Will you be able to save the club and start a brand new life? Can you trust Monika in this altered reality? Will it finally be the renewal that we've all been waiting for?

_data.title: The Rising Night
_data.description: This mod focuses on the lives of two MC's, taking place just a few days before the 'festival' and in the eyes of the new MC; A very unenthusiastic high school student who always keeps to himself and is generally more introverted. His more mysterious, reserved nature usually results in him taking a backseat (or just staying out of) most social environments, seeing no use in getting involved in any types of extracurricular activities. On the other end of the spectrum, there's the normal MC who's already established in the club and preparing for said 'festival'. He's the one we all know and love, so I'm sure you'll know him already. That said, the lives of our main protagonists are soon to change in ways they couldn't have ever expected, both good and bad.

_data.title: The Post Credit Scene
_data.description: What if DDLC had a special scene at the end teasing a potential sequel? this is merely a what if scenario with a lil meta humor. you don't need to replay the entire game again to see the scene just replace the files as you do with other mods and just start a new game! if you have a minute or 2 to spare then this is the mod for you!

_data.title: The Window, The Desk, and The Violet
_data.description: A MC is a stranger to the Literature Club and enters in to see a distant friend. An uninviting atmosphere shifts him in front the club's local nerd. Their time together in one club meeting is tightly stuck between the chairs they sit on and the desk the between them. As both squirm uncomfortably through the conversation, perhaps MC can close the distance of his new and old relationships, a word at a time. The Window, The Desk, and The Violet provides a short 1 hour experience of genuine, grounded, and--uh.... pretty awkward conversation as young angsty teenagers with horrific and barely passable skills of social interaction as they try to make sense of one another! TWTDATV honestly stays true to its minimalistic setting with you and the grape for a sweet playthrough to the end!

_data.title: Thot Club
_data.description: Instead of thinking about what it would be like if MC saved the dokis, why not wonder what it would be like if MC hated them? Speaking of MC, what if he was an All American boi that had some very strong political (Conservative) beliefs? Well, we answer these questions with Doki Doki Thot Club, because the club is filled with hella thots. (We have a very mutual respect for our beloved dokis, which brings us to say that no dokis were harmed during the making of this mod, .--- -.-)Also, this mod is pretty NSFW in some ways, and some of the views that are presented in this mod can be offensive to some people. This mod, by no means should be taken seriously. Overall it should be taken as a joke.

_data.title: The Yuri Parable
_data.description: Do you like the The Stanley Parable? Do you like Doki Doki Literature Club? Have you ever wished that the two games would crossover? Do you like tedious questions that are asked purely to generate intrigue? If you answered  yes  to any of the prior questions, you are in luck!The Yuri Parable is an experience for those looking for a comedic adventure focused around a certain pen-loving bookworm (cough cough Yuri cough cough), alongside a very handsome narrator. The Yuri Parable does not assume any fault nor can it be sued for any  terrible jokes  it might produce.

And of course, to make a story that made sense. While a few things were added majority of the assets came from chiffmonkey's folder.Enjoy our protagonist's reminiscence over his highschool years.

_data.title: True Happiness
_data.description: The story starts off with our protagonist not remembering any of the club members. As he starts regaining his memories, he finds a purpose: to save all of the girls of the literature club! Will he be able to overcome the challenges he has to face? Will you find a bitter or a sweet ending? Play it for yourself and find out!

_data.title: Tutorial!
_data.description: A mod that finally gives a proper tutorial for upcoming modders, expanding on the Modding Template and the subreddit's modding tutorial. What do you mean that's not what the mod's about? Did I miss something?

_data.title: Twin Realities
_data.description: In DDLC Twin Realities, you play as a NEET, like Sayori would say. You're a nerd, a loner, an outcast- who's about to change his life. After Monika put you in her space room you refused to delete her. Instead, you wrote mod after mod to spend time with Monika. Monika is controlled by an intelligent AI and she can react to things that happen by herself. In each mod you write dialogue for MC, so that he can react, talk, and have fun with Monika. But it never felt real.Until now.Your dad received a mysterious package from your late uncle. He was a great inventor who died before he could finish his inventions. Your dad decides to leave for the week and throw the things away later, but you know better. With your technology skills you manage to finish a most peculiar device nicknamed the Reality Machine: Made to transport people to and from a virtual world. Here is your plan. You are going inside DDLC, build four copies of the machine in the game, and let the girls use the device to come to your reality.

_data.title: Undercurrents
tags: route, full_cast, n_visual, n_music, n_gplay, n_char, spec_eff, world_b
_data.description: Introducing the full demo for Doki Doki Undercurrents, a snapshot of the first Act of the story, split into four branches and following the ever-stubborn Melody. Experience the highs and lows of familiar and unfamiliar faces, and learn what it means to be human as you step into the shores of this expansion. Be careful not to be swept away in the process...

_data.title: Vigilante
_data.description: This mod is about a highschool boy who moves back into his childhood neighbourhood after 5 years. Just as he settles into his surroundings, he is granted a special power that he must carry responsibly.Includes demo for Chapter 2.

_data.title: Ultimate Combo
_data.description: Ever wanted to play ComboDev's mod on your own? Well, now, you can! You'll be able to play the old and new mods anytime!Editor's note: Since this is a compilation of many mods, it's mixed genre-wise. Alongside romance you'll find comedy, horror and serious drama within this mod.Please read the content warning section before playing.

_data.title: Undone Fate
_data.description: When Monika retains her memories of the previous playthrough, events go down differently than in the base game. How differently? Well, the inclusion of a whole new week to play through for starters! But be warned: Just because Monika is no longer messing with the game's code doesn't mean there are no more tragedies that can go down in the Literature Club... Can you Undo the tragic Fate this game is pushing for and ensure a happy ending?Editor's note: The beginning of this mod is mostly the same as Act 1 of DDLC, albeit with minor changes.

_data.title: We are the Literature Club
_data.description: This story was created to continue on the story of the Literature Club, and to give the girls the ending that they deserved, as well as the closure that the player thought they would never get.Set in an alternate canon, where the meddlings of the class president never took place, We are the Literature Club carries on the story by laying a new foundation in storytelling, eventually culminating in the revival of the Literature Club for a new era.With a small cast of new characters, and familiar ones, We are the Literature Club sets the stage for an enjoyable "re-write" of the world of Doki Doki Literature Club, with a slight twist in an alternate timeline.After all that happened; are you really willing to let it end there?"

_data.title: Weatheard World
_data.description: A story revolving around the club president Monika, and her drive to create a new world. A new world for her, and for You, the player. But this decision must be made wisely, as sacrifices will be warranted. Just how big of a sacrifice is needed?But perhaps  maybe Monika isn't the one pulling all of the strings now?Editor's note: Please, take this mod with a pinch of salt  and a bag of pop corn.

_data.title: Welcome to the Anime Club
_data.description: MC and Monika: Once best friends, now bitter enemies with the former trying to close the Literature Club for good. One game. One gamble might decide the future for both clubs. Will this gamble bring him good fortune or will it contribute to his own demise and the LC gets to live for another day?

_data.title: Welcome to Doki Doki Literature Club, Player!
_data.description: Welcome to Doki Doki Literature Club, Player! is a mod about a player who ends up in the world of DDLC. The mod is loosely based on the fan fiction of the same name by finalsacre.

_data.title: West Virginia Club
_data.description: This mod was supposed to have a story focused on West Virginian issues and made comedic light and commentary on them. Such as teen pregnancy, drug addiction, incest, and the KKK. As of now, the game had all of act one rewritten, a festival added, and a good 1/3rd of Monika's route written and coded.Notes from the author: link. (only read after you played the mod)Editor's note: You'll need to delete 'scripts.rpa' from your game folder before running this mod.

_data.title: What if...?
_data.description: Life only goes on one set path and yet, the mind can’t help but wonder what could’ve happened. What if things happened differently? What if I did this instead of that? What if I was better? Let this mod take you on a journey which stares at the fate of DDLC and asks… What If? Who knows? We might learn something new on the way.

_data.title: We are the Literature Club II
_data.description: A parody of Rockstar Games' Red Dead Redemption II in DDLC's style, bringing to life a new arc in We Are The Literature Club's story. Set during a heavily competitive festival revolving around literature (in which the whole town is in on), the Literature Club does everything in their power to collect the most literature out of all the attending clubs. This leads to the club president doing everything she can to win, which sometimes results in her ambition getting the best of her. Caught in the crossfire is our protagonist, who is trying to make the best of the situation.It falls on you to help him make the right choices. Will you be able to help the other club members cope, or focus on more selfish means to resolve the conflicts that arise?

_data.title: What If+
_data.description: Life only goes on one set path and yet, the mind can’t help but wonder what could’ve happened. What if things happened differently? What if I did this instead of that? What if I were to disguise fast food as my own cooking? Let this mod take you on a journey which stares at the fate of DDLC and asks… What if what if? Who knows? We might escape our wretched fates finally.

_data.title: World of Dreams
_data.description: A certain player (With a first and last name so keep that in mind when naming your character) is thrust into the world of Doki Doki Literature Club. He finds himself possessing the body of the game's protagonist, Meiji Chizu. However, Meiji is still around, just relegated to backseat driver in his own body. Together, along with Monika, they try to prevent the events of the original game from happening. Will they succeed? Or will they fail? And remember, the game doesn't end...until the credits are over.

_data.title: Window to Your Heart
_data.description: In Window to Your Heart, you play a brand new MC: a transfer student cursed with a special gift. This mod takes place after an alternate version of DDLC's Act 1, leading to the dissolution of the literature club. At Monika's request, it's your job to reform the club as well as the girls' friendship before graduation.

_data.title: XD
_data.description: This is a rom-com mod with a lot of fluff and risqué humor, inspired by the game dev studio SMEE. It has a lot of references to other VNs and some of my favorite media. It's not gonna be for everyone, but I hope it can get a chuckle out of someone at least.

_data.title: World of Walker
_data.description: Main Character, who graduated from high school, moves to France, abandoning his friends from the literature club to the mercy of fate. But fate throws up a series of unexpected coincidences and occurrences. From that moment Main Character is on a psychological journey with old and new acquaintances, not imagining how much he is connected with new characters. This plot is not canonical history of original World Of Walker. Reference: World of Walker is a cinematic universe created by Norwegian producer Alan Walker and director Kristian Berg.
